Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_well_tap_mode(25.10)                              set_well_tap_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_well_tap_mode - Controls the behavior of addWellTap command

Syntax
       set_well_tap_mode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-abut_boundary_tap_distance  {{<cell1  cell2 distance1>} {<cell1 cell3
       distance1>} {<cell2 cell3 distance3>} ... }]

       [-antenna_tap_break_cell <cell_list>]

       [-antenna_tap_cell <cell_list>]

       [-antenna_tap_left_cell <cell_list>]

       [-antenna_tap_pitch <microns>]

       [-antenna_tap_right_cell <cell_list>]

       [-antenna_tap_right_top_edge_cell <cell_list>]

       [-avoid_vertical_well_abutment {none|ntap|ptap|all_tap}]

       [-avoidAbutment {true|false}]

       [-block_boundary_only {true | false}]]

       [-bottom_tap_cell cellName]

       [-bottom_termination_cell <cellList>]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-channel_offset <offset_value>]

       [-check_channel {true|false}]

       [-column_cell <cellList>]

       [-create_rows {true|false}]

       [-disable_check_zone_at_boundary {none|vdd|vss|both}]

       [-inRowOffset <offset_value>]

       [-insert_cells <cellName  rule  dense_layer  dense_rule  boundary_layer
       boundary_rule>]

       [-rule microns]

       [-siteOffset <number_of_sites>]

       [-tap_function_cells <cell_list>]

       [-tap_termination_alignment {true|false}]

       [-termination_align {left|right|center}]

       [-termination_cell <cellList>]

       [-top_tap_cell <cellName>]

       [-top_termination_cell <cellList>]

       [-vertical_boundary_spacing <spacing_with_well_tap>]

       [-well_cut_cell <cellList>]

       Controls  the  behavior of addWellTap command. The mode setting is per-
       sistent and saved along with the database by the saveDesigncommand. Use
       get_well_tap_mode to return the current settings for  set_well_tap_mode
       command.

       Note:  Parameters  specified  by the addWellTap command supersede those
       specified by the set_well_tap_mode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each set_well_tap_mode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man set_well_tap_mode.

       -abut_boundary_tap_distance {{<cell1 cell2 distance1>} {<cell1 cell3
       distance1>} {<cell2 cell3 distance3>} ... }
              Specifies  the  boundary  cells and their tap distance when they
              are vertically abutted. If you do not set this option, the  abut
              cell  still  uses  the single cell distance. If you specify this
              option, the abut cell tap cover distance uses  the  defined  new
              value.  You need to add additional tap cell at the area when the
              tap cell checkboard cannot cover it.

              This parameter works for the N4 process.

              You can control the tap distance of  a  single  cell  using  the
              set_well_tap_mode  -tap_function_cells  {<cellnames rule value>}
              parameter.

              Default: ""

       -antenna_tap_break_cell <cell_list>
              Specifies the cells that would break the tap ground connection.

              Default: ""

       -antenna_tap_cell <cell_list>
              Specifies the normal antenna tap cell.

              Default: ""

       -antenna_tap_left_cell <cell_list>
              Specifies the antenna tap cell names of the left boundary edge.

              Default: ""

       -antenna_tap_pitch <microns>
              Specifies the pitch of antenna tap cell. It should be  twice  of
              the TAP protect distance.

              Default: 0

       -antenna_tap_right_cell <cell_list>
              Specifies the antenna tap cell names of the right boundary edge.

              Default: ""

       -antenna_tap_right_top_edge_cell <cell_list>
              Specifies the antenna tap cell names of the right incorner.

              Default: ""

       -avoid_vertical_well_abutment {none|ntap|ptap|all_tap}
              Specifies  which type of well-tap cells to be forbidden from the
              vertical abutment.

              Default: none

       -avoidAbutment {true|false}
              Specifies whether the inserted taps should avoid horizontal  and
              vertical abutment.

              Default: false

       -block_boundary_only {true|false}
              Specifies  whether to insert termination tap cells only for well
              tap columns on the block boundary. Default is false, termination
              cells are inserted on both core boundary row and block  boundary
              row.

              Note:  This  parameter  works  only  when  inserting termination
              cells.

       -bottom_tap_cell <cellName>
              Specifies well taps inserted into bottom  rows  during  enclosed
              end cap insertion.

              Note:  This  parameter  must  be  specified  when `setEndCapMode
              -boundary_tap true'.

       -bottom_termination_cell <cellList>
              Specifies the list of bottom termination cells to be used.

              Default: ""

       -cell  Specifies the name of the cell in the technology library to  use
              as a well-tap. The cell should be of class type CORE.

              Default: ""

       -channel_offset <offset_value>
              Specifies the offset value between taps and blockage in channel.

              Default: 0

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 1.79769313486232e+308

       -check_channel {true|false}
              Specifies whether the blockage channel will be checked.

       -column_cell <cellist>
              Specifies  the  list  of well tap columns that need to be termi-
              nated. This parameter must be specified for termination tap cell
              insertion.

       -create_rows {true|false}
              Creates rows for welltap cell techSites which do not  have  rows
              in the floorplan.

              Default: false

       -disable_check_zone_at_boundary {none|vdd|vss|both}
              Disables the check zone at boundary.

              Default: none

       -inRowOffset <offset_value>
              Specifies  the  distance  between the first welltap in a row and
              the start of the row.

              Default: 0 (first cell in  beginning  of  row  is  the  starting
              point)

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 1.79769313486232e+308

       -reset Resets all or specified options to the default value.

              Any  values  that do not already match the default value and are
              reset will be reported.

       -insert_cells <cellName rule dense_layer dense__rule boundary_layer
       boundary_rule>
              Inserts well-taps based on cell, layer, and interval.

              * cellName: Specifies the cell name.

              * rule: Cell with this rule would be added as a general tap cell
                for all placeable area. The center to center  spacing  of  tap
                cells  would  be  <=  (2*$rule)  without  -checkerBoard and <=
                (4*$rule) with -checkerBoard.

                Note: Center of the tap cell is used to check the spacing.

              * <dense_layername>: Specifies the dense layer name.

              * dense_rule: Cell with dense layer would be added to the  given
                layer  regions  only.  Cell  with  dense layer must follow the
                dense rule. The center to center spacing of  dense  tap  cells
                would  be  <=  (2*$dense_rule) without -checkerBoard and <= (4
                *$dense_rule) with -checkerBoard.

              * <boundary_layername>: Specifies the boundary layer name.

              * boundary_rule: A cell would be added for boundaries inside the
                given layer regions. The cell must follow the  boundary  rule.
                The spacing between the boundary to the center of boundary tap
                cells  would  be  <=  $  boundary rule. Boundary layer regions
                which cover partial sites should be  extended.  Boundary  taps
                can be located in or out of boundary layer regions.

              Note:

              * You  can define multiple cells for -insert_cells by separating
                each cell by { }.

              * There should be at lest one  rule,  dense  layer  or  boundary
                layer, defined for each cell.

              * The order of tap cell insertion is:

              *

                * Dense tap

                * Boundary tap

                * General tap

              *

                If the area is covered by both dense layer region and boundary
                layer region, both layer rules must be satisfied.

              *

                If  -insert_cells  is defined multiple times, the last setting
                is accepted by the tool.

              * If -insert_cells is defined, you  do  not  need  define  -rule
                while using the verifyWellTap command.

       -rule  Specifies the rule to be honored when adding well taps.

              To  define  multiple  TAP  rules in a design , addWellTap parses
              TAPDISTANCE defined in the cell LEF and Tech LEF.  It  works  on
              the following conditions:

              * If  you  do  not define set_well_tap_mode -rule, the tool will
                use the LEF rule.

              * If both set_well_tap_mode -rule and LEF rule  are  not  speci-
                fied, the tool will error out.

              * If  there are multiple tap distance values defined in the Tech
                LEF, addWellTap will take the smallest value.

              * For existing tap cells, you need to use addWellTap  -incremen-
                tal.  If  you specify a tap cell with tap distance bigger than
                the incremental cell, the tool will add the cell and  print  a
                warning message.

       -siteOffset <number_of_sites>
              Specifies  an offset value, in number of sites, so that the ver-
              tical taps are aware of.

       -tap_function_cells <cell_list>
              Defines the endcap cells which have tap functions.  Use  of  tap
              function  cells  reduces the number of tap cells to be inserted.
              The defined endcap cells are treated as tap function cells  dur-
              ing  the tap cell insertion. The tool will consider the tap dis-
              tance between welltap cell and the defined endcap cell with  tap
              function.

              To insert tap cells considering the tap function not only on the
              checkboard  but also on the termination tap cell insertion flow,
              addWellTap treats the endcap cell as a tap  function  cell  when
              set_well_tap_mode -tap_function_cells is set.

              The   verifyWellTap   command   honors   the   set_well_tap_mode
              -tap_function_cells settings to check the tap distance.

              Default: ""

       -tap_termination_alignment {true|false}
              Specifies whether to align well-taps and termination cells.

              Default: false

       -termination_align {left|right|center}
              Specifies the termination cell alignment.

              Default: left

       -termination_cell <cellList>
              Specifies the list of cells that  can  be  used  as  termination
              taps.  The  command  addWellTapselects  the best fit termination
              cells from this list and inserts them at the top and  bottom  of
              well  tap column segment. The existing non-termination well taps
              are deleted as needed. If the well tap columns have already been
              terminated with a valid termination cell, the existing  termina-
              tion  cell  are  kept  in the incremental run and no changes are
              made.

              Note: It is recommended that well tap columns are  added  before
              termination cell insertion.

              Note:  This parameter must be specified for termination tap cell
              insertion.

       -top_tap_cell <cellName>
              Specifies well taps inserted into top rows during  enclosed  end
              cap insertion.

              Note:  This  parameter  must  be  specified  when  setEndCapMode
              -boundary_tap is set to  true.

       -top_termination_cell <cellList>
              Specifies the list of top termination cells to be used.

              Default: ""

       -vertical_boundary_spacing <spacing_with_well_tap>
              Specifies the spacing between center of tap  cell  and  vertical
              boundary

              Default: -1

              Minimum: -1

              Maximum: 1.79769313486232e+308

       -well_cut_cell <cellist>
              Specifies  the list of cells with the well cuts. addWellTap con-
              siders the specified cells cutting the row.

Related Information
              * addWellTap

              * saveDesign

              * setEndCapMode

              * verifyWellTap

